        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 28. Phyllodoce tamoya sp. nov. A, anterior end in dorsal view; B, detail of everted proboscis in dorsal view.Anterior view of parapodia. C, parapodium 12; D, parapodium 40; E, parapodium 80; F, detail showing bilobed and symmetrical parapodial lobes; G–I, compound spinigerous chaetae; J, pygidium and anal cirri in regeneration; L, cylindrical anal cirri and anal papilla, ventral view Scale bars: Scale bars: A, 1.0 mm; B, 0.08 mm, C, 0.015 mm; D–E, 0.055 mm, F, 0.04 mm; G, 0.002 mm; H, 0.002 mm, J, 0.05 mm; L, 0.05 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4496869/files/figure.png" .

